  "riddle": "1. Seek the founder whose lineage claims descent from the ancient city that holds the essence of Jammu.\n\n2. How many volumes did the scholar from the Jamwal clan contribute to the world of literature?\n\n3. Before you proceed, take the number of books you unearthed and reverse its digits.\n\n4. Identify the last ruler of the region whose legacy intertwined with the name of the Dogra dynasty. \n\n5. What year marked the end of the reign for the sovereign whose lineage began with Gulab Singh?\n\n6. Ascend to the heights of the ruler's domain — how high does it stand above sea level?\n\n7. Count how many places of worship for Christians lie in the shadows of this royal residence.\n\n8. Combine the elevation you gathered in clue 6 with the tally of churches from clue 7 — what do you discover?\n\n9. Discover the reign dates of the monarch known for his notable changes in the Jammu territory.\n\n10. Determine how many vowels compose the name of the ruler you just found.\n\n11. What date marked a significant declaration during the turmoil that followed the violent events of 1947?\n\n12. Seek the height above sea level where the tragedies of that year unfolded.\n\n13. In the vicinity of the events of 1947, how many temples stand aloft, paying homage to belief?\n\n14. Now, take the elevation noted in clue 12 and merge it with the number of temples you found in clue 13 — what is the total?\n\n15. The city where the royal palace stands has an elevation of what?\n\n16. Reveal the answer by summing the digits of the elevation found in clue 15.\n\n17. From the date of the turmoil in 1947 until mid-March 2026, how many days will have passed?\n\n18. Once more, determine the span in days from the defining moment in 1947 to the year 2026.\n\n19. Finally, combine the year you discovered in clue 5 with the count of temples from clue 13, then compute: (clue 5 + clue 13) % 10. What single digit emerges from this calculation?",
